paperparcel

Annotation Type Adapter


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=SOURCE)
 @Target(value={})
public @interface Adapter
    Used in conjunction with ProcessorConfig to add a custom TypeAdapter to PaperParcel's type system.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends TypeAdapter> value
        The TypeAdapter class to register into PaperParcel's type system.

      • nullSafe

        public abstract boolean nullSafe
        Return true if this TypeAdapter can handle nulls or doesn't need to (i.e. the TypeAdapter is parcelling a non-nullable type). If this returns false (the default), then PaperParcel will do null-checking for you. Returning true from this method can help by preventing double (or completely unnecessary) null-checking.
        Default:
        false
